1) a method that returns the sum of two integers

START 
GET integer1
verify input
GET integer2
verify input
SET sum = integer1 + integer2
PRINT sum
END

2) a method that takes an array of strings and returns a string that is all
those strings concatenated together

START
verify input array is strings
SET result_string = nil
WHILE index < length
  append new string to result_string 
PRINT result_string
END

3) a method that takes an array of integers and returns a new array with 
every other element

START
verify input array is integers
SET result_array = []  
WHILE index < length
  IF index is even
    append integer at this index to result_array
PRINT result_array 
END
